    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 3, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 Hormuz got another small-boat attack while diplomats reread the proposal\n\nThe ceasefire-adjacent shipping lane remains very committed to not acting like a shipping lane.\n\n- **The attack:** AP reported on May 3 that a northbound cargo ship near Sirik, Iran, was attacked by multiple small craft east of the Strait of Hormuz.\n- **The status:** all crew were safe, and there was no immediate claim of responsibility.\n- **The pattern:** AP counted at least two dozen attacks in and around the strait since the Iran war began.\n\n*The war may be negotiating. The waterway is still filing incident reports.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/454006a0a9bb19a45a2f299c0869cefb)\n\n---\n\n## 🧾 Iran sent a 14-point plan, because apparently the war needed homework\n\nWashington asked for a pause. Tehran sent a full checklist and moved the nuclear file to later. Smooth.\n\n- **The proposal:** Al Jazeera reported on May 3 that Iran sent the U.S. a 14-point plan with nonaggression guarantees, sanctions relief, asset releases and an end to the war on all fronts.\n- **The mismatch:** Washington wants a two-month ceasefire; Tehran wants issues settled within 30 days and nuclear talks postponed.\n- **The pressure:** the IRGC says it is ready for a return to war, while Trump says he doubts the plan can produce a deal.\n\n*Diplomacy has entered the spreadsheet phase, which is never a sign of simplicity.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera](https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2026/5/3/iran-war-whats-happening-on-day-65-as-trump-reviews-new-plan-to-end-war)\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ China blocked U.S. refinery sanctions and called the rulebook fake\n\nThe oil route around Iran now comes with a sanctions fight, a ministry statement and five refineries in the middle.\n\n- **The move:** China's Commerce Ministry announced an injunction against U.S. sanctions on five Chinese independent refiners accused of importing Iranian oil.\n- **The argument:** Beijing said the measures improperly restrict Chinese business with third countries and violate international norms.\n- **The U.S. claim:** Treasury had called Hengli one of Tehran's most valued customers and said its crude purchases generated hundreds of millions of dollars for Iran's military.\n\n*The sanction is American. The refusal is Chinese. The oil, inconveniently, keeps being oil.*\n\n**Sources:** [Al Jazeera and Reuters](https://www.aljazeera.com/economy/2026/5/3/china-blocks-us-sanctions-against-five-teapot-refineries)\n\n---\n\n## 🛳️ Ukraine hit Russia's Baltic oil port while Kherson took the drone bill\n\nThe war map keeps stretching: Baltic terminals, Black Sea logic, and civilians still stuck at the local stop.\n\n- **The long strike:** Reuters reported on May 3 that Ukrainian drones hit Russia's Primorsk port, setting fires and striking a Karakurt-class missile ship, a patrol boat and an oil tanker.\n- **The stated aim:** Zelenskyy said each result limits Russia's war potential.\n- **The civilian cost:** AP reported that a Russian drone killed two people and wounded seven in a Kherson minibus attack on May 2.\n\n*Strategic depth is great copy until the return receipt lands on a city bus.*\n\n**Sources:** [Reuters via MarketScreener](https://www.marketscreener.com/news/ukrainian-drones-hit-russia-s-primorsk-port-oil-tankers-and-military-ships-ce7f58dedb8df422) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/04d3404205efdf7311991a0d86fe17d5)\n"
  }
]
